One man was killed and three others hurt during a shooting at a Brooklyn social club Saturday afternoon, police and sources said. The incident unfolded around 1:45 p.m. at 491 East 45th St., near Snyder Avenue in the East Flatbush section, cops said. The dead man, 39, has not been publicly identified, the NYPD said. Two women and another man were also injured. Police are investigating.Â There have been no arrests.